   <note>Stresses that the seizure and destruction of arms for Arkansas is an act of rebellion. Asks if the guilty parties and the Avalanche, the newspaper which incited the rebels to the act, will be allowed to go unpunished. Foresees this as the beginning of a new revolt by Tennessee`s rebels. Expresses the hope that Governor Brownlow will use militia in curbing disorders.</note>
